ttp://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Bull_BC_One\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first woman\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has since won at the 2021 WDSF World Breaking Championship in Paris, where the competition was split into men and women categories.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999327990303, \"rank\": 6.720096754566199e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"WDSF World Breaking Championship\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 927}, {\"ngram\": \"men and women categories\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also took bronze at the 2022 World Games and 2023 Asian Games in Hangzhou, China.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1039, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.468881987245304e-15, \"text\": \"Hangzhou\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hangzhou\"}, {\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.707197323320779, \"rank\": 0.40541993733131554, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 World Games\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1014}, {\"ngram\": \"2023 Asian Games\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fukushima first dabbled in breakdancing as a shy 21-year-old student.\",